'''Charles Monginda Pickel''' (born 15 May 1997) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for {{Spanish football updater|Espanyol}} club [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]]. Born in Switzerland, he plays for the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]].

==Club career==
[[File:RC Lens - Grenoble Foot 38 (10-02-2020) 60.jpg|left|thumb|Pickel with [[Grenoble Foot 38|Grenoble]] in 2020|250x250px]]
Pickel started his youth football with [[FC Solothurn]]. In Summer 2011, he transferred to the youth department of [[FC Basel]] and played in their U-16 and advanced via their U-17 and U-18 team to their U-21 team in 2015. On 23 December 2015, he signed a two-and-a-half-year professional contract, but remained with the U-21 team.<ref name="fcb-aktuell-2015-pickel-vertrag">{{cite web | first = | last = FC Basel 1893 | author-link = | date = 3 December 2015 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/alle-news/2015/12/charles-pickel-unterzeichnet-einen-profivertrag | title = Charles Pickel unterzeichnet einen Profivertrag | format = | work = Charles Pickel signs his first professional contract | publisher = FC Basel 1893 AG | language = de | access-date = 2022-11-16}}</ref> On 16 May 2016, Pickel was called up to the first team by head coach [[Urs Fischer (footballer)|Urs Fischer]]. He played his [[Swiss Super League]] debut for the Basel first team in the starting eleven, but Basel suffered a 0–4 away defeat against [[FC Luzern|Luzern]].<ref name="fcb-aktuell-">{{cite web | first = Caspar | last = Marti | author-link = | date = 16 May 2016 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/1-mannschaft/2016/05/04-der-fcb-bleibt-ohne-chancen-beim-fc-luzern | title = 0:4 – Der FCB bleibt ohne Chancen beim FC Luzern | format = | work = 0:4 – FCB had no chance against FC Luzern | publisher = FC Basel 1893 AG | language = de | access-date = 2022-11-16}}</ref> Basel won the [[Swiss Super League]] championship at the end of the [[2015–16 Swiss Super League|2015–16 Super League season]]. For the club it was the seventh title in a row and their 19th championship title in total.<ref name="SRF-2015/16-19. Title">{{cite web | first = | last = SRF | author-link = | date = 30 April 2016 | url = https://www.srf.ch/sport/fussball/super-league/fc-basel-holt-den-19-meistertitel | title = FC Basel holt den 19. Meistertitel | format = | work = FC Basel wins their 19th championship title | publisher = Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen (SRF) | language = de | access-date = 2022-11-16}}</ref>

Pickel joined Basel's first team definitively for their [[2016–17 FC Basel season|2016–17 season]] under head coach [[Urs Fischer (footballer)|Urs Fischer]]. Although he appeared in ten test matches, he played only one more [[Swiss Super League|league]] match, with the team in the home game in the [[St. Jakob-Park]] on 4 February 2017 as Basel won 4–0 against [[FC Lugano|Lugano]].<ref name="fcb-achiv-2016/17-FCB-Lugano">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | author-link = | date = 4 February 2017 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=31139 | title = FC Basel - FC Lugano 4:0 (3:0) | format = | work = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | access-date = 2022-11-16}}</ref> Basel announced on 1 March that Pickel was leaving the club.<ref name="Telebasel-pickel-gc">{{cite web | first = Melanie | last = Kägi | author-link = | date = 1 March 2017 | url = https://telebasel.ch/2017/03/01/charles-pickel-wechselt-zum-grasshopper-club-zuerich/?channel=105110 | title = Charles Pickel wechselt zum Grasshopper Club Zürich | format = | work = Charles Pickel is moving to Grasshopper Club Zurich | publisher = Telebasel online | language = de | access-date = 2022-11-16 | archive-date = 21 November 2022 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20221121180017/https://telebasel.ch/2017/03/01/charles-pickel-wechselt-zum-grasshopper-club-zuerich/?channel=105110 | url-status = dead }}</ref> With the U-21 Pickel had played 38 goals scoring three goals. During a short time with Basel's first team Pickel played a total of 13 games without scoring a goal. Three of these games were in the [[Swiss Super League]] and ten were friendly games.<ref name="fcb-achiv-Charles Pickel">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | authorlink = | year = 2022 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/spieler?command=detail&id=9634 | title = Charles Pickel - FCB statistic | format = | work = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | accessdate = 2022-11-16}}</ref>

On 1 March 2017, Basel announced that Pickel had signed for [[Grasshopper Club Zürich|Grasshopper Club]].<ref name="fcb 2017-03-01">{{cite web | last = FC Basel 1893 | author-link = | year = 2017 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/de-CH/News/2017/02/28/Charles-Pickel-wechselt-zum-Grasshopper-Club-Zueri | title = Charles Pickel wechselt zum Grasshopper Club Zürich | format = | publisher = FC Basel 1893 | access-date = 1 March 2017 | archive-date = 5 March 2017 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170305041513/https://www.fcb.ch/de-CH/News/2017/02/28/Charles-Pickel-wechselt-zum-Grasshopper-Club-Zueri | url-status = dead }}</ref> GC announced that he had signed a four-and-a-half-year contract with them.<ref name="gc 2017-03-01">{{cite web | last = GCZ | author-link = | year = 2017 | url = http://www.gcz.ch/news/news/artikel/milan-vilotic-und-charles-pickel-zu-gc | title = Charles-Pickel zu GC | format = | publisher = Grasshopper Club Zürich | access-date = 1 March 2017}}</ref> Pickel played his debut for his new club on 5 March 2017 in the [[Swissporarena]] in the starting eleven against [[FC Luzern|Luzern]]. He played the entire game and it ended in a 1–1 draw.

On 1 July 2019 GC announced that Pickel was transferring to [[Grenoble Foot 38|Grenoble]].<ref name="GC-Pickel-Grenoble">{{cite web | first = | last = Grasshopper Club Zürich | author-link = | date = 1 July 2019 | url = https://www.gcz.ch/news/news/artikel/charles-pickel-wechselt-zu-grenoble/ | title = Charles Pickel wechselt zu Grenoble | format = | work = Charles Pickel joins Grenoble | publisher = gcz.ch | language = de | access-date = 2022-11-16}}</ref>

On 22 July 2022, it was announced that Pickel had joined newly promoted [[Serie A]] club [[U.S. Cremonese|Cremonese]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=22 July 2022 |title=Pickel nuovo calciatore della Cremonese |url=https://www.uscremonese.it/pickel-nuovo-calciatore-della-cremonese/ |access-date=22 July 2022 |website=U.S. Cremonese |trans-title=Pickel is the new player of Cremonese |archive-date=11 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220811012003/https://www.uscremonese.it/pickel-nuovo-calciatore-della-cremonese/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Switzerland, Pickel is of [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Congolese]] and Swiss descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://leopardleader.com/2019/05/15/portrait-de-charles-pickel/|title=Portrait de Charles Pickel|first=par|last=Kad|date=15 May 2019|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-date=1 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221001044920/https://leopardleader.com/2019/05/15/portrait-de-charles-pickel/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Pickel played one international game for the [[Switzerland national under-15 football team|Swiss U-15]]. He played his debut for the [[Switzerland national under-18 football team|Swiss U-18]] as midfielder on 2 September 2014 as they drew 2–2 with the [[Sweden national under-18 football team|Swedish U-18]]. He played his debut for the [[Switzerland national under-19 football team|Swiss U-19]] as [[Defender (association football)|defender]] on 1 September 2015 as they drew 1–1 with [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal U-19]].<ref name="SFV 2015-09-01">{{cite web | last = SFV | author-link = | year = 2015 | url = http://www.football.ch/de/SFV/Nationalteams/U-19/Das-Team-U-19.aspx/p-628840 | title = Kader U-19 Charles Pickel | format = | publisher = SFV | access-date = 1 September 2015}}</ref> His last game for the [[Switzerland national under-20 football team|Switzerland U-20]] was on 27 March 2018 in the away game against [[Italy national under-20 football team|Italy U-20]], where Pickel played as right-back and the Swiss won 3–2.

Pickel was called up to the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]] for a set of [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] matches in September 2023.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://actualite.cd/index.php/2023/08/24/elimcan-2023-avec-pelly-ruddock-mpanzu-et-charles-monginda-pickel-la-liste-de-sebastien | title=Elim/CAN 2023 : avec Pelly-Ruddock Mpanzu et Charles Monginda Pickel, la liste de Sébastien Desabre pour le Soudan | date= 24 August 2023 }}</ref> He debuted with them in a 2–0 win over [[Sudan national football team|Sudan]] on 9 September 2023, assisting his side's first goal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://supersport.com/football/africa-cup-qual/news/f6a00aa8-5799-413d-b9bd-8af43438b9e9/dr-congo-secure-afcon-qualification|title=DR Congo secure Afcon qualification|website=SuperSport}}</ref>

